---
const checks = [
  'A real trial before the paid IPTV subscription continues',
  'Supported apps, including IPTV Smarters when your plan allows it',
  'Smart TV, Fire TV, Android, iOS, browser, and console setup notes',
  'Live football coverage details before checkout',
  'Clear renewal terms, cancellation rules, and support contact options',
];

const reasons = [
  {
    title: 'Football comes first',
    body: 'The service path is built around live football and World Cup 2026 viewing, not a vague channel list.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Plans are readable',
    body: 'Choose 1 month, 3 months, 6 months, or 12 months without guessing what each IPTV plan costs.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Setup matters',
    body: 'Check your TV, phone, tablet, IPTV player, console, or browser during the 24-hour trial.',
  },
];
---

<section
  id="iptv-service"
  aria-label="How to choose an IPTV service"
  class="relative w-full scroll-mt-20 bg-canvas px-6 py-16 md:px-12 md:py-20"
>
  <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-coreMaxWidth">
    <div class="mx-auto mb-12 max-w-3xl text-center">
      <p class="mb-3 text-[12px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.125em] text-ch-yellow">
        IPTV service guide
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-balance text-3xl font-bold leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.0357em] text-white md:text-5xl">
        What is IPTV, and how do you choose the right service?
      </h2>
      <p class="speakable-answer mx-auto mt-5 max-w-2xl text-base leading-[1.55] text-body md:text-lg">
        IPTV means Internet Protocol Television. In plain English: your live TV stream comes through the internet instead of a cable or satellite box. Good IPTV services make pricing, app support, device setup, and cancellation terms clear before checkout.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-4 grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-3">
      <article class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-surface-card p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold leading-tight text-white">
          IPTV
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-[1.6] text-body">
          IPTV is the broad term. People search it when they want to understand internet TV, live channels, sports streams, device setup, or whether IPTV is a fit for their home.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-surface-card p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold leading-tight text-white">
          IPTV service
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-[1.6] text-body">
          The service is the provider side: plans, access details, support, app compatibility, renewal terms, and the live football coverage you expect to watch.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-surface-card p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold leading-tight text-white">
          IPTV Smarters
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-[1.6] text-body">
          IPTV Smarters is a popular player. It does not replace the provider. You still need a compatible subscription and login details from the service you choose.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_1.15fr]">
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-surface-card p-6 md:p-7">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold leading-tight text-white">
          What to check before buying an IPTV subscription
        </h3>
        <ul class="mt-6 space-y-3">
          {
            checks.map((check) => (
              <li class="flex gap-3 text-sm leading-[1.55] text-body">
                <span class="mt-2 h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-ch-yellow"></span>
                <span>{check}</span>
              </li>
            ))
          }
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3">
        {
          reasons.map((reason) => (
            <article class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-surface-card p-5">
              <h3 class="text-base font-bold leading-tight text-white">
                {reason.title}
              </h3>
              <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-[1.55] text-body">
                {reason.body}
              </p>
            </article>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="speakable-answer mx-auto mt-8 max-w-3xl text-center text-sm leading-[1.6] text-muted">
      IPTV World Cup helps customers compare IPTV providers, live football plans, FIFA World Cup 2026 viewing options, and an IPTV subscription that works across common household devices.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
